Program: Start the Week
Title: Political Divide: Mary Robinson and Michael Ignatieff
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01npgn5
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 5 Nov 2012
Start the Week is at BBC Radio 3's Free Thinking Festival in Gateshead to debate whether the world is becoming a more divided place. Andrew Marr discusses the state of politics with the former President of Ireland Mary Robinson and the writer-turned-politician Michael Ignatieff, while the Israeli author Amos Oz asks whether entrenched ideas have increasingly polarised debate. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less